<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="L" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Leading" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Leading,</orth> 1) command, direction: <cit><quote>his eye commends the l. to his hand,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 436" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 436</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.3.130" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 3, 130</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.297" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 V, 3, 297</bibl>. <cit><quote>if thou wilt have the l. of thine own revenges,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 4.5.143" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. IV, 5, 143</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) generalship: <cit><quote>being men of such great l. as you are,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.3.17" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A IV, 3, 17</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>